oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Music City Queen on a Cumberland River voyage, n.d.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The “Music City Queen” pictured on a Cumberland River voyage. Music City Queen was a replica showboat formerly operating for entertainment purposes on the Cumberland River in the southern United States. It was the smaller of two stern-wheel paddle steamers based at Opry Mills in Nashville, Tennessee; the other is the General Jackson.Forms part of the Bill Goodman Photographic Slides Collection. 1 35 mm negative.
